{{Quote|What is this place?''"<br />"''I don't know, I've never seen anything like it, not even in Atlantis.|Short Round and Indiana Jones while aboard the remains of the ''Millennium Falcon''|<ref name="Into">{{Tales|19|Into the Great Unknown}}</ref>}}
'''Atlantis''' was a location that was at one point visited by [[Doctor/Legends|Doctor]] [[Indiana Jones]]. While exploring the wreck of a [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300 light freighter]] called the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Earth/Legends|Earth]], Jones commented to his companion [[Short Round]] that he had never witnessed a place like it, including in Atlantis.<ref name="Into" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Fate_of_Atlantis.png|thumb|right|200px|Indiana Jones explored Atlantis in ''Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis''.]]
Atlantis was mentioned in "[[Into the Great Unknown]]," a [[Canon|non-canon]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] written by [[W. Haden Blackman|Haden Blackman]] and published by [[Dark Horse Comics]] in ''[[Star Wars Tales]]''{{'}} [[Star Wars Tales 19|nineteenth issue]]<ref name="Into" /> on [[May 14]], [[2004]].<ref name="Date">{{Marvel|url=comics/issue/53997/star_wars_tales_1999_19|text=Star Wars Tales (1999) #19}}</ref> The comic portrays a crossover with the [[W:c:IndianaJones:Indiana Jones (franchise)|''Indiana Jones'' franchise]], in which the eponymous character had explored the ancient lost city of [[W:c:IndianaJones:Atlantis|Atlantis]] in the Dark Horse Comics series [[W:c:IndianaJones:Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis (comic)|''Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis'']],<ref name="Comic">[[W:c:IndianaJones:Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis (comic)|''Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis'' comic]]</ref> the first issue of which was released on [[March 1]], [[1991]].<ref name="Date 2">{{DarkHorse|url=Comics/91-258/Indiana-Jones-and-the-the-Fate-of-Atlantis-1-of-4|text=Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis #1 (of 4)}}</ref> The series adapted the [[1992]] [[LucasArts]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] of the [[W:c:IndianaJones:Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis|same name]].<ref name="Fate">[[W:c:IndianaJones:Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis|''Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis'']]</ref> Prior to the game's release, Atlantis was mentioned in a ''[[Star Wars]]'' related source in a preview for the game that was included in the [[The Adventurer 3|third issue]] of the LucasArts magazine ''[[The Adventurer]]'', released in Fall 1991.<ref name="Adventurer">{{AdventurerCite|3|Indiana Jones and the Fate of Atlantis|nolink=1}}</ref> In the real world, [[Wikipedia:Atlantis|Atlantis]] is a legendary sunken island described in the dialogues of [[Wikipedia:Plato|Plato]],<ref name="Brittanica Atlantis">{{WebCite|url=https://www.britannica.com/topic/Atlantis-legendary-island|text=Atlantis|archivedate=20210224181828}}</ref> an [[Wikipedia:Ancient Greece|Ancient Greek]] philosopher.<ref name="Brittanica Plato">{{WebCite|url=https://www.britannica.com/topic/Plato|text=Plato|archivedate=20211226023142}}</ref>

